00:44:06.000 --> 00:44:07.400
do I want to build?

00:44:07.400 --> 00:44:10.370
I also hope that this
information helps you

00:44:10.370 --> 00:44:13.210
build that strong design team.

00:44:13.210 --> 00:44:16.520
Now this brings me to the
last part of my presentation

00:44:16.520 --> 00:44:19.660
where I promise to share some
advice for designers who are

00:44:19.660 --> 00:44:21.480
interested in designing for VR.

00:44:21.480 --> 00:44:25.120
So I have two tips
and won advice.

00:44:25.120 --> 00:44:28.700
Tip number one, learn
from your own experiences.

00:44:28.700 --> 00:44:30.620
If you are new to
VR, get a cardboard,

00:44:30.620 --> 00:44:34.380
throw your phone in, try out
as many VR apps as you can.

00:44:34.380 --> 00:44:36.420
Keep a journal of
your observations.

00:44:36.420 --> 00:44:38.370
Gradually you'll start
developing an eye

00:44:38.370 --> 00:44:40.290
for the nuances of VR.

00:44:40.290 --> 00:44:43.150
You'll start identifying what
works, what doesn't work.

00:44:43.150 --> 00:44:45.540
And if you start feeling
that urge to make things,

00:44:45.540 --> 00:44:48.550
then follow the second tip,
which is learn the tools.

00:44:48.550 --> 00:44:51.120
As a VR designer you might
need to learn these three

00:44:51.120 --> 00:44:52.090
categories of tools.

00:44:52.090 --> 00:44:54.790
And if you're a designer, you
only already know one of these.

00:44:54.790 --> 00:44:56.760
You need to focus on
the remaining two.

00:44:56.760 --> 00:45:00.100
I would recommend you to
start with a gaming engine.

00:45:00.100 --> 00:45:02.240
Both Unity and Unreal are free.

00:45:02.240 --> 00:45:04.090
And they are tons
of online material

00:45:04.090 --> 00:45:05.891
that can help you get started.

00:45:05.891 --> 00:45:07.890
You know, it's very
important to get comfortable

00:45:07.890 --> 00:45:09.760
with these tools,
because this will

00:45:09.760 --> 00:45:13.570
let you focus your mind space
on what to create and not on

00:45:13.570 --> 00:45:15.940
how to create.

00:45:15.940 --> 00:45:17.580
And lastly I'll be honest.

00:45:17.580 --> 00:45:19.660
You know the learning
curve is steep.

00:45:19.660 --> 00:45:22.010
You will need to be really
passionate about VR are

00:45:22.010 --> 00:45:24.730
and persistent to get
over this learning. curve.

00:45:24.730 --> 00:45:28.250
One thing that helps is being
part of the VR community.

00:45:28.250 --> 00:45:30.830
It can give you enough
support and inspiration

00:45:30.830 --> 00:45:33.350
to help you keep climbing
up this learning curve.

00:45:33.350 --> 00:45:35.320
And, hey, it might look
like a tough climb.

00:45:35.320 --> 00:45:37.930
But the rewards come
very early and they are

00:45:37.930 --> 00:45:40.120
very satisfying and fulfilling.

00:45:40.120 --> 00:45:42.190
So don't give up.

